  <discussion type="conservation">of conservation concern;</discussion>
  <discussion>Calydorea coelestina blooms well only after a fire. The flowers open at sunrise and last about three hours. The species is rare, but not currently threatened. A single collection from Camden County, southern Georgia (Schallert s.n., UC) requires confirmation.</discussion>
